id: pm-395t
title: "SDK client.run() rejects structured payloads for create: raw {type,title} fails with 'Missing required option --title'"
description: "SDK client.run currently rejects structured create payloads such as raw {type,title}; the fix should accept typed structured inputs or return a precise SDK-facing error instead of CLI flag parsing text."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[2]: "area:sdk",dx
created_at: "2026-07-06T21:53:02.655Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-07T02:53:35.600Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: "client.run('create', ...) either accepts bare title/type keys by mapping them to CLI flags, or the split-args contract is documented in docs/SDK.md with a typed error pointing callers to client.create(); regression test covers both paths"
parent: pm-usfg
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: "PmClient.run('create', structuredPayload) now hoists top-level create keys into action options and is covered by SDK temp-tracker tests."
expected_result: Package authors can pass structured create payloads without nesting every field under options.
actual_result: Structured title/type/status/createMode payloads create items successfully through PmClient.run and full coverage passed.
