body: "Found during audit #12 external CJS-host verification (note on pm-rjqr): raw client.run('create', {type,title}) fails with 'Missing required option --title' because run() expects pre-split argv-style args, while the typed client.create() works. Agents composing SDK calls dynamically will hit this. Either map structured payload keys onto flags inside run(), or document the contract and emit a helpful error suggesting the typed primitive."
